The paper deals with network compression and control plane behavior, which are topics related to computer networks and communication (cs.NI). It also involves the preservation of network properties such as reachability and loop freedom, which are related to systems and control (cs.SI). The algorithm developed in the paper involves the compression of large networks, which is a topic related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions simulation, emulation, and verification, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves the development of a new theory of control plane equivalence, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
